{
  "texts": [
    "To this end, using a window size of 51 residues, we calculated the local end-to-end distance across every 51-mer fragment in the human proteome, enabling us to extract the 2,146,400 51-mer fragments that lay entirely within every IDR (Fig. 5a).",
    "With our definition of a highly compact/expanded window falling in the bottom/top 2.5%, this analysis generates just over 50,000 highly compact/expanded subregions (Fig. 5b).",
    "We used previously published protein abundance data from HeLa cells to identify highly abundant proteins with ten or more compact or expanded subregions 51.",
    "For IDRs with compact subregions, almost all are RNA-binding proteins, with many known to undergo homotypic phase separation, a result consistent with the presence of an IDR with favorable intramolecular interactions (Fig. 5c) 16, [52] [53] [54].",
    "For IDRs with expanded subregions, many are histones, reflecting the positively charged histone tails, along with additional abundant RNA-binding residues drive compaction, while proline drives expansion."
  ]
}